{"title": "Quiet Hints to Growing Preachers", "description": "Charles Edward Jefferson was pastor of the Broadway Tabernacle in Brooklyn, New York for 33 years. In Quiet Hints, published in 1901, he provided guidance to young preachers on what we would today call ministerial deportment, an old-fashioned word that refers to how a man carries himself, how he presents himself, his manners, his bearing, his habits, and his whole approach to life. Jefferson wrote in short, pithy statements that encapsulate practical truth in just a few words. (Summary by MaryAnn)", "duration": 12605, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "606", "name": "Charles E. Jefferson"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt13/quiet_hints_1201.jpg", "copyright_year": "1901", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Religion", "Self-Help"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Barry Eads"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Joy Easton"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - Wherefore All This", "readers": [3645], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quiet_hints_1003_librivox/quiethints_01_jefferson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 471}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - A Mirror for Ministers", "readers": [3645], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quiet_hints_1003_librivox/quiethints_02_jefferson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 451}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - The Man of Macedonia", "readers": [3645], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quiet_hints_1003_librivox/quiethints_03_jefferson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 461}, {"section": 4, "title": "04 - Which Door?", "readers": [3645], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quiet_hints_1003_librivox/quiethints_04_jefferson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 470}, {"section": 5, "title": "05 - Starts Good and Bad", "readers": [3645], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quiet_hints_1003_librivox/quiethints_05_jefferson_64kb.mp3", "duration":